g.text: If you have any questions please email j.a.pike@bham.ac.uk
This workflow is for the semi-automated segmentation of touching touchs in 2D. The user manually anotates images to select the center
of each cell. A watershed transformation is then used to fill the cellular regions as defined by a ilastik pixel classification project. Output
statistics for each cell are saved as an excel file.
Most of the user defined parameters
Use this node to seed cells
Use this node to visualise the
Use this node to visualise the output
Can optionally be used to crop the field
ERROR Labeling Arithmetic 0:130:111 Execute failed: java.lang.IllegalStateException: Incompatible IterationOrder
Cause: The "Interactive Annotator" node hasnt reset properly after a change in the size of the field of view
- Insert a new "Interactive Annotator" node (drag and drop from the "Node Repositry") and connect as before
- Within the "Interactive Annotator" node "Column Selection" tab change "Column creation mode" to "Append"
- Under the "Label Settings" tab change "Storage Img Type" to "INTTYPE"
ERROR Ilastik Headless (Pixel classification) 0:175:27:2 Execute failed: java.io.IOException: Cannot run program "C:\Program Files\ilastik-
1.2.0\ilastik.exe": CreateProcess error=2, The system cannot find the file specified
Cause: The ilastik path is not configured properly within KNIME
- First make sure ilastik is installed
- Within KNIME File -> Preferences -> Image Processing Plugin -> Ilastik
- Make sure the "Path to Ilastik installation" option is specifiying the ilastik.exe file for your ilastik installation
Only load data for the segmentation
